## 🛠️ Environmental Architecture & Kill-Chain Flow

The offensive assessment operations are orchestrated exclusively from an isolated Kali Linux architecture pointing directly into an untrusted corporate subnet template.

```
[ Initial Onboarding User ] 
           │
           ▼
[ SharpHound Ingestion Sweep ] ──> [ BloodHound Path Graph Analysis ]
                                                   │
                                                   ▼
                                      [ ACL Abuse (GenericAll) ]
                                                   │
                                                   ▼
                                     [ Kerberoasting / AS-REP Roast ]
                                                   │
                                                   ▼
                                      [ DCSync Account Dumping ]
                                                   │
                                                   ▼
                                      [ Golden Ticket Persistence ]

```

### Lab Specifications

* **Attacker System OS:** Kali Linux (hosting core database servers, BloodHound graph suites, and protocol execution frameworks).
* **Target Workstation Environment:** Windows 11 Enterprise (simulating victim operational workspaces).
* **Domain Infrastructure Host:** Windows Server 2019 (acting as the authoritative Domain Controller for `pentestlab.local`).

> [!NOTE]
> Per rigorous testing guidelines, zero administrative credentials to the Windows Server platform are supplied upfront. Comprehensive infrastructure access must be won cleanly through remote enumeration, relationship mapping, and exploit orchestration from the Kali Linux testing machine.

