## 🔬 Forensics & Event Correlation Cheat Sheet

A crucial component of this project is understanding the footprints left behind during escalation. The following Event IDs track the lifecycle of the attack chain:

| Attack Stage | Vector / Mechanism | Definitive Windows Event ID |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Authentication** | Kerberos TGS Ticket Request (Kerberoasting) | `4769` (Ticket Granting Service requested with weak cipher) |
| **Authentication** | Kerberos AS-REP Request (AS-REP Roasting) | `4768` (Authentication Ticket requested without pre-auth) |
| **Privilege Abuse** | Directory Replication Abuse (DCSync) | `4662` (An operation was performed on an object - DS Replication) |
| **Persistence** | Golden Ticket Utilization | `4624` (Successful Logon using forged/anomalous parameters) |
| **Execution** | Malicious PowerShell Activity | `4104` (PowerShell Script Block Logging capture) |

