## 🔧 Deployment & Core Operational Tooling

To replicate the graph compilation and execution sequences built natively inside this workspace environment:

### 1. Ingesting Active Directory State

Execute the execution collection binary directly from an established user shell within the target ecosystem to dump the state catalog files:

```powershell
.\SharpHound.exe --CollectionMethod All --Domain pentestlab.local

```

### 2. Running the Analytical Graphic Frontend

Initialize the localized graph query environment inside the Kali Linux testing console:

```bash
# Start the underlying Neo4j graph storage engine
sudo neo4j start

# Launch the visual analysis client mapping interface
bloodhound

```

*Drag-and-drop the generated SharpHound `.zip` archive data dump directly into the user interface to instantly construct complex lateral path visualization models.*

