## 🔒 Defensive Architecture (Remediation Design)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To defend enterprise domains against graph-mapped path attacks, blue teams must move away from point-in-time perimeter defense and apply systemic hardening controls:
> 1. **Clean Up Object ACLs:** Audit and strip explicit control permissions (e.g., `GenericAll`, `WriteDacl`) granted to non-administrative groups over high-value users or objects.
> 2. **Enforce Tiered Administration:** Isolate domain administrator accounts, ensuring they never log into lower-tier workstations where their credential material could be cached and extracted.
> 3. **Protect Replication Permissions:** Strictly restrict the `Get Changes All` directory synchronization permissions to legitimate Domain Controllers, immediately breaking the capability to execute unauthorized **DCSync** attacks.
